WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:05.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In the day's other news: Federal
Reserve Board Chair Janet
Yellen affirmed that short-term

00:05.900 --> 00:10.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
interest rates are likely to
rise again in the coming months.

00:10.333 --> 00:14.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But she also left the door
open to changing those plans.

00:14.266 --> 00:19.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Yellen told a congressional
hearing that a recent slowdown
in inflation might make the

00:20.133 --> 00:22.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Central Bank recalculate.

00:22.100 --> 00:24.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANET YELLEN, Federal Reserve
Chair: Monetary policy is
not on a preset course.

00:24.666 --> 00:29.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're watching this
very closely, and stand
ready to adjust our
policy if it appears that

00:32.833 --> 00:35.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the inflation undershoot
will be persistent.

00:35.500 --> 00:40.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Separately,
Yellen said the Fed could begin
to unload its massive bond

00:41.266 --> 00:43.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
holdings this year.

00:43.333 --> 00:47.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It bought government bonds
during and after the recession
in order to lower long-term

00:47.333 --> 00:50.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
interest rates and to
boost economic activity.

00:50.866 --> 00:54.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Wall Street took heart
from Yellen's talk of
going slow on rate hikes.

00:54.666 --> 00:59.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial
average gained 123
points to close at 21532.

01:01.466 --> 01:03.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's a new record.

01:03.066 --> 01:07.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The Nasdaq rose nearly
68 points, and the
S&amp;P 500 added 17.

01:09.833 --> 01:14.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of Brazil's former
presidents, Luiz Inacio
Lula da Silva, was convicted
today in a sweeping

01:15.400 --> 01:17.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
corruption probe.

01:17.966 --> 01:21.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A judge sentenced him
to 9.5 years in prison,
but for now he remains
free, pending his appeal.

01:23.800 --> 01:28.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Silva served as president from
2003 to 2010, and is still
widely admired in Brazil.

01:31.033 --> 01:36.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Saudi Arabia today, U.S.
Secretary of State Rex Tillerson
held talks, but made no apparent

01:37.900 --> 01:41.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
progress in ending a
boycott of another Persian
Gulf nation, Qatar.

01:43.800 --> 01:46.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tillerson met with King Salman,
and later the Saudi crown
prince, in the city of Jiddah.

01:48.366 --> 01:51.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Later, he flew to Kuwait, and
returns to Qatar tomorrow.

01:51.700 --> 01:56.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Saudis and other Arab
states have accused Qatar
of financing terrorism.

01:58.700 --> 02:01.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In Turkey, President Recep
Tayyip Erdogan has rejected
any talk of lifting a state of

02:02.766 --> 02:04.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
emergency.

02:04.800 --> 02:08.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He imposed it last July
after rogue soldiers
tried to overthrow the
government, killing

02:09.666 --> 02:11.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
more than 240 people.

02:11.733 --> 02:16.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Erdogan visited graves of the
victims yesterday, and he told
international investors meeting

02:17.866 --> 02:21.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in Ankara today that disloyal
elements are still at large.

02:21.200 --> 02:23.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RECEP TAYYIP ERDOGAN, Turkish
President (through translator):
What are we supposed to do with

02:23.400 --> 02:24.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
all this happening?

02:24.633 --> 02:26.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They say lift the
state of emergency.

02:26.600 --> 02:28.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This won't happen.

02:28.233 --> 02:30.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
I had an interview
with an international
media organization.

02:30.033 --> 02:32.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They asked if the state
of emergency will finish.

02:32.900 --> 02:36.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It will finish when this
business is completely
out of the way.

02:36.000 --> 02:41.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Erdogan's
opponents say that he has used
emergency rule to quash dissent.

02:42.933 --> 02:47.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There is word that Chinese
political dissident and Nobel
peace laureate Liu Xiaobo is now

02:48.300 --> 02:50.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in critical condition.

02:50.266 --> 02:55.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A hospital in Shenyang,
reported today he is suffering
multiple organ failure.

02:55.966 --> 02:58.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Liu has late-stage liver cancer.

02:58.266 --> 03:03.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He was released from prison on
medical leave just last month.

03:05.333 --> 03:08.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Back in this country, the Royal
Bank of Scotland has agreed on a
settlement with U.S. regulators,

03:09.300 --> 03:12.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and will pay $5.5 billion.

03:12.200 --> 03:17.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It involves claims that the
bank sold billions of dollars of
toxic mortgage-backed securities

03:18.333 --> 03:21.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
before the 2008
financial meltdown.

03:21.600 --> 03:26.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And President Trump lost
his nominee today to
lead the Federal Deposit
Insurance Corporation.

03:29.000 --> 03:32.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
James Clinger cited
family-related obligations
that had prompted him
to leave government

03:32.100 --> 03:34.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
service earlier this year.

03:34.066 --> 03:36.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He said that they have grown
more challenging in the interim.
